            If you click on the first button at the top 
            &#160;<graphic fileref="../../../resources/images/arrow_out.png" align="center" valign="middle"/>&#160;, 
            all folders are opened fully, where all folders close up if you click the second
            &#160;<graphic fileref="../../../resources/images/arrow_in.png" align="center" valign="middle"/>&#160;. 
            The third button
            &#160;<graphic fileref="../../../resources/images/arrow_refresh.png" align="center" valign="middle"/>&#160;, 
            the one for reloading the folder view, is only needed if you work for a long time on the database and new folders that you can see have been created (or deleted) by others since you logged in - these you will only be able to see if you reload the Folder View.
        </para><para>
            When you click on a folder or a folder name and thereby select it, you will see that the "path" leading to the folder from the base folder, "mods", separated by slashes, in the manner of "/mods/Cluster_publications", in the search panel. 
        </para><para>
            Clicking on a folder in this way is how you determine where to perform a search. If you search for something, it will be searched for inside the path you have chosen. 
        </para>
